org.panthercode.arctic.core.helper.version

Class Version

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.panthercode.arctic.core.helper.version.Version
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Freezable

    public final class Version
extends java.lang.Object
implements Freezable
    This class is used to control and manage objects by version. The scheme follows the major.minor[.build[.revision]] pattern.

      • fromAnnotation

        public static Version fromAnnotation(java.lang.Object object)
        Create a new version from the annotation information given by the object. If the annotation is empty or the object has no annotation at all a default identity object is returned.
        Parameters:
        object - object with annotation
        Returns:
        Returns a new version object made of annotation information.

      • parse

        public static Version parse(java.lang.String version)
                     throws java.lang.NumberFormatException
        Parse a string to an version object. The function splits the string at each "." character and converts the parts to numbers. If the string contains other characters than numeric ones an exception is thrown. If the string has more than 4 parts the rest is ignored. This function is synchronized.
        Parameters:
        version - version as string
        Returns:
        Returns a new version object.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - Is thrown if the string contains not only numeric characters.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a string representing the version object. The function always returns the major and minor number, also in case one value or both are zero. If the build or revision number is zero the value is ignored, expect the build number is zero and revision number is greater zero the full version is print out.

        Example: 1.0.0.0 returns 1.0, 1.0.1.0 returns 1.0.1 and 1.0.0.1 returns 1.0.0.1

        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        Returns a string representing the version object.
